## API Testing Patterns

### TxnStatus (Internal PG Status) — Patterns
```java
// Pattern A: fluent chain validation (preferred for standard PGOnly tests)
TxnStatus txnStatus = new TxnStatus(orderDTO.getMID(), orderDTO.getORDER_ID());
txnStatus.executeUntilNotPending();  // polls until not PENDING (max 1 minute)
txnStatus.validateStatus("TXN_SUCCESS")
         .validateRespCode("01")
         .validateOrderid(orderDTO.getORDER_ID())
         .validateTxnAmount(orderDTO.getTXN_AMOUNT())
         .AssertAll();               // note: AssertAll() with capital A

// Pattern B: getter-based soft assertions after executeUntilNotPending
TxnStatus txnStatus = new TxnStatus(orderDTO.getMID(), orderDTO.getORDER_ID());
txnStatus.executeUntilNotPending();
SoftAssertions softly = new SoftAssertions();
softly.assertThat(txnStatus.getResponse().getRESPCODE()).as("RESPCODE").isEqualTo("01");
softly.assertThat(txnStatus.getResponse().getSTATUS()).as("STATUS").isEqualTo("TXN_SUCCESS");
softly.assertThat(txnStatus.getResponse().getORDERID()).as("ORDERID").isEqualTo(orderDTO.getORDER_ID());
softly.assertAll();

// Pattern C: raw response for one-shot execute (no polling)
TxnStatus txnStatus = new TxnStatus(orderDTO.getMID(), orderDTO.getORDER_ID());
Response rawResponse = txnStatus.execute();  // single call, sets txnStatusResponse internally
softly.assertThat(rawResponse.jsonPath().getString("STATUS")).isEqualToIgnoringCase("TXN_SUCCESS");
// NOTE: getResponse() returns TxnStatusResponse (POJO getters only), not a raw RestAssured Response.
// For jsonPath access use the rawResponse variable from execute() above — there is no getApiResponse() method.
```

### GetPaymentStatus (Merchant-Facing Status API) — Patterns
```java
// For PGOnly: use 2-param constructor (aggrMid is null for PGOnly — never pass orderDTO.getAggrMid())
GetPaymentStatusDTO dto = new GetPaymentStatusDTO.Builder(
        orderDTO.getORDER_ID(), Constants.MerchantType.PGOnly)
        .build();

// For merchants where you have explicit mid + key:
GetPaymentStatusDTO dto = new GetPaymentStatusDTO.Builder(
        orderDTO.getORDER_ID(), orderDTO.getMID(), merchant.getKey())
        .build();

// Execute and assert on JsonPath
Response gpsResponse = new GetPaymentStatus(dto).execute();
JsonPath jsonPath = gpsResponse.jsonPath();
SoftAssertions softly = new SoftAssertions();
softly.assertThat(jsonPath.getString("body.resultInfo.resultStatus")).as("resultStatus").isEqualToIgnoringCase("TXN_SUCCESS");
softly.assertThat(jsonPath.getString("body.resultInfo.resultCode")).as("resultCode").isEqualTo("01");
softly.assertThat(jsonPath.getString("body.orderId")).as("orderId").isEqualToIgnoringCase(orderDTO.getORDER_ID());
softly.assertThat(jsonPath.getString("body.mid")).as("mid").isEqualToIgnoringCase(orderDTO.getMID());
softly.assertThat(jsonPath.getString("body.txnAmount")).as("txnAmount").isNotEmpty();
softly.assertAll();
```

### CRITICAL: API Class Creation Checklist
**BEFORE creating any new API class, ALWAYS follow this mandatory checklist:**

1. **Search Existing API Classes** - Use codebase search to find existing API classes for the same endpoint
2. **Check API Endpoint Mapping** - Verify if the endpoint is already covered by existing API classes
3. **Review Existing Implementation** - Analyze existing API class structure and patterns
4. **Determine Reusability** - Check if existing API class can be extended or modified
5. **Avoid Duplication** - Only create new API class if no suitable existing implementation exists

**Search Commands to Use:**
```bash
# Search for existing API classes by endpoint
grep -r "setBasePath.*\/api\/your-endpoint" src/main/java/com/paytm/api/
grep -r "your-endpoint" src/main/java/com/paytm/api/
grep -r "YourApiName" src/main/java/com/paytm/api/

# Search for similar API patterns
grep -r "extends BaseApi" src/main/java/com/paytm/api/
```

**If API class already exists:**
- **Extend existing class** instead of creating new one
- **Add new methods** to existing class if functionality is related
- **Create wrapper methods** in existing class for new requirements
- **Document the extension** with proper comments

**Only create new API class if:**
- No existing API class covers the endpoint
- Existing API class cannot be extended due to architectural constraints
- New API class serves a completely different purpose


### API Class Structure
```java
public class YourApiClass extends BaseApi {

    public YourApiClass(String param) {
        setMethod(MethodType.POST);
        getRequestSpecBuilder().setBaseUri(LocalConfig.PGP_HOST);
        getRequestSpecBuilder().setBasePath("/api/endpoint");
        getRequestSpecBuilder().addHeader("X-Amzn-Trace-Id", PGPHelpers.TraceIdGenerator());
        getRequestSpecBuilder().setContentType(ContentType.JSON);
    }

    // Use existing response handling patterns
    public void executeUntilGetResponse(int timeOutInSeconds, int pollingTimeInSeconds) {
        Response response = null;
        int pollCount = 0;
        long startTime = System.currentTimeMillis();

        while ((System.currentTimeMillis() - startTime) < timeOutInSeconds * 1000) {
            pollCount++;
            response = this.execute();
            if (response.getStatusCode() == 200) {
                break;
            }
            // Existing polling logic
        }
        Assertions.assertThat(response.getStatusCode()).as("Status Code").isEqualTo(200);
    }
}
```

### DTO Builder Pattern
```java
public class YourRequestDTO {
    private String field1;
    private String field2;

    // Use existing builder pattern
    public static class Builder {
        private String field1;
        private String field2;

        public Builder setField1(String field1) {
            this.field1 = field1;
            return this;
        }

        public YourRequestDTO build() {
            return new YourRequestDTO(this);
        }
    }

    // Use existing constructor pattern
    public YourRequestDTO(Builder builder) {
        this.field1 = builder.field1;
        this.field2 = builder.field2;
    }
}
```

## UI Testing Patterns

### Page Object Structure
```java
public class YourPage extends BasePage {

    public YourPage() {
        super("Page Display Name");
    }

    // Use existing element patterns
    private Button submitButton() {
        return new Button(By.id("submitBtn"), getPageName(), "Submit Button");
    }

    private TextBox cardNumberField() {
        return new TextBox(By.id("cardNumber"), getPageName(), "Card Number Field");
    }

    // Use existing action patterns
    public void performAction() {
        submitButton().click();
        waitUntilLoads();
    }

    // Use existing validation patterns
    public void validateExpectedAndActual(String fieldName, String actual, String expected) {
        if (actual.equals("FIELD_NOT_AVAILABLE_IN_UI")) {
            this.softly.fail(fieldName + " field not available in UI");
        } else {
            this.softly.assertThat(actual).as(fieldName + " mismatch").isEqualToIgnoringCase(expected);
        }
    }
}
```

